According to Ghana&#8217;s soccer news website, GhanaSoccerNet.com, Gyimah was driving with a female passenger when he collided with a taxi JOHANNESBURG Ghanaian media is reporting that Orlando Pirates defender Edwin Gyimah was involved in a car accident in the early hours of Monday. According to Ghana s soccer news website, GhanaSoccerNet.com, Gyimah was driving with a female passenger when he collided with a taxi in his hometown of Obausi.Gyimah is said to have sustained minor injuries, while his passenger had to be rushed to the nearest hospital.Orlando Pirates is yet to comment on the reports.